OL,3,C#16 billion down? That's not entirely
OL,4,Ctrue Prime Minister
OL,6,FExplaining why taxes are rising again
OL,7,Fafter promising they wouldn't was
OL,8,Falways going to be tricky.
OL,10,FThis morning, the prime minister
OL,11,Fsought to defend the narrative the
OL,12,Fgovernment pushed in the run-up to the
OL,13,FBudget.
OL,15,F"I started off #16 billion down," Sir
OL,16,FKeir insisted at a press conference, a
OL,17,Freference to the worst outlook for
OL,18,Fgrowth handed to the government by the
OL,19,FOffice for Budget Responsibility (OBR).
