OL,3,C#16 billion down? That's not entirely
OL,4,Ctrue Prime Minister
OL,6,F1. The PM is technically correct: the
OL,7,FOBR said the productivity downgrade
OL,8,F"could" cut tax revenues by #16
OL,9,Fbillion.
OL,11,F2. But, as the OBR said, higher
OL,12,Finflation and wage growth "more than
OL,13,Foffset this". By 2029/30, tax revenues
OL,14,Fwere forecast to be #16 billion higher
OL,15,Fthan in March.
OL,17,F3. Extra government spending of #22
OL,18,Fbillion on welfare and debt interest,
OL,19,Fhowever, brought the net impact back
OL,20,Finto the red.
