OL,3,C#16 billion down? That's not entirely
OL,4,Ctrue Prime Minister
OL,6,FIt's understandable that there was a
OL,7,Fpolitical temptation to blame the
OL,8,Fproductivity downgrade, which the
OL,9,Fchancellor cannot reasonably be held
OL,10,Fresponsible for, but the spinning went
OL,11,Ftoo far.
OL,13,FThe Budget has landed in a way that
OL,14,Fhas left many people feeling misled -
OL,15,Fat a time when public trust in both
OL,16,Fthe chancellor and the prime minister
OL,17,Fis extremely low.
